      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/4/2/10",
      "text": [
        " \"إِلاَّ أَنْ تَزْنِيَ فَتُخْرَجَ وَ يُقَامَ عَلَيْهَا اَلْحَدُّ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4759 - Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) was asked about the saying of Allah (swt), the Mighty and Majestic: \"And fear Allah (swt), your Lord (azj). Do not expel them from their houses, nor should they leave unless they commit a clear immorality\" (Surah At-Talaq 65:1).\nImam (as) replied: \"Except if she commits adultery, then she is to be expelled, and the prescribed punishment (ḥadd) is to be carried out upon her.\""
        ]
      }
    },
